channel.title: Get on any website at school, new way
channel.description:
dont do this if you think you will screw up your computer
this will make it so proxy servers cant be blocked and so that a proxy server cant steal your passwords
go to run type regedit press ctrl + F search proxyserver (no spaces) TWICE delete everything other than the one called (default)
[b]EDIT[/b] if run is blocked go to C:\windows\system32\regedt32.exe or C:\windows\regedit.exe
works on most... careful not to get caught :|

item.title: Get on any website at school, new way
item.dc:creator: @ThAt0n36Uy Elijah
item.description:
@ThAt0n36Uy wrote:

At my school we have Regedit blocked, but Run works, though they blocked most of the features within run. We also have Task manager etc, but we cannot end system processes, or one started by another user. We have most everything else, at one point the blocked access to the C:/ drive, but then returned it, with copy and paste, or cut and paste options blocked within system folders. I run extra programs to stylize my desktop, and use FireFox and Pidgin to instant message. I really don’t try to bypass anything online, I used to, but it was occasional, and only when I wanted something, like a file. Not to play games. We also have a program called GenevaLogic, which monitors our actions, like an administrator computer can watch and see all that we do. They also have control over our mouse and keyboard. And internet access.
